  **RMC Section**   §18-408(d)                       §18-408(e)

  **Eligibility**   Any active member before normal  Post-1962: 10 yrs credited
                    retirement date                  svc. Post-1988: 5 yrs
                                                     credited svc.

  **Cause**         Compensable injury/occupational  Disease or accidental
                    disease arising out of and in    injury (NOT from felony or
                    the course of employment         intentional
                                                     self-infliction)

  **Timing Req.**   Injury within 24 months before   Post-2005: Disease/injury
                    retirement date (exceptions      within 24 months
                    possible post-2005)              (exceptions possible)

  **SS Disability** SS must award disability for     Same requirement
                    same impairment (or physician    
                    cert if SS-ineligible)           

  **Application**   Within 90 days of termination    Same requirement
                    due to disability                

  **Completion**    Requirements met within 3 years  Same requirement
                    of termination (extensions       
                    possible)                        

  **Benefit         §18-409(c): Higher of 20 yrs or  §18-409(d): Higher of 75%
  Formula**         actual+10 yrs (max to age 65)    of service-duty calc or
                                                     early retirement amount

  **Effective       First of month following         Same
  Date**            termination                      

  **Death w/in      Deemed active member at date of  Same
  36mo**            death                            

  **Cessation**     Re-employment above SGA. SS      Same
                    denial/suspension/termination.   
  ----------------- -------------------------------- --------------------------

6.2 Disability Benefit Formulas

**Service-Duty Disability --- §18-409(c)** (§18-409(c))

> The member receives the benefit they would be entitled to at normal
> retirement, calculated using the HIGHER of: (a) 20 years of service,
> or (b) actual service plus 10 years. In either case, the service used
> cannot exceed what the member would have earned to age 65. This is a
> generous provision --- it gives credit for hypothetical future
> service.

**Non-Service Disability --- §18-409(d)** (§18-409(d))

> The member receives the HIGHER of: (a) 75% of the service-duty
> disability amount calculated per §18-409(c), or (b) the early
> retirement amount calculated per §18-409(b). This comparison ensures
> members with substantial actual service get at least their early
> retirement amount even if the 75% formula would yield less.

6.3 Disability Death Benefit

**RMC:** §18-411(d)(4-5)

At or after age 65: \$5,000. Before age 65: 1.5 times the member's
annualized average monthly salary, limited to \$50,000. This amount
reduces to \$5,000 when the disabled member reaches age 65. This is
significantly more generous than the normal/early retirement death
benefit schedule.

6.4 Temporary Early Retirement Pending Disability

**RMC:** §18-408(f)

A member who has applied for disability retirement may elect temporary
early retirement (if eligible) while the disability application is
pending. If disability is approved, a retroactive adjustment is paid. If
disability is not qualified within 3 years from the temporary early
retirement date, the member receives a regular early retirement. During
this period, death benefits follow the early retirement schedule, not
the disability schedule.

6.5 Post-2005 Changes

The RMC defines two eras of disability requirements with a boundary at
August 1, 2005. The post-2005 provisions (§18-408(d)(2) and (e)(2)) are
more detailed and slightly more flexible:

**Pre-Aug 2005:** Required permanent medical impairment rating ≥26% or
equivalent Workers' Comp schedule of 175+ weeks. Plus SS disability
award. No extension provisions.

**Post-Aug 2005:** Requires 'final admission of liability' from
employer. SS disability OR physician certification if SS-ineligible.
24-month and 3-year requirements can be extended by executive director
for good cause.

6.6 Implementation Considerations

**Complexity assessment:** Disability retirement is the most complex
benefit type in the DERP system. It involves: (1) Two benefit formulas
with hypothetical service projections; (2) Cross-agency verification
(Workers' Comp, SS Administration, employer risk management); (3)
Multi-year processing windows with extension authority; (4) Interaction
with early retirement as a temporary bridge; (5) Ongoing medical review
authority; (6) Cessation triggers tied to external employment and SS
status. This should be a later-phase implementation with dedicated
process orchestration.

